  "text": "with µ, ν = a or b, and a k (b k ) is the amplitude of ψ a,b over the plane wave of momentum k. We assume identical interactions in states a and b with a coupling constant g = 4π 2 a/m where a is the s-wave scattering length while states a and b do not interact (g ab = 0). Note that the coupling constant in H a,b should actually be a bare coupling constant g 0 different from the effective coupling constant g, but this difference can be made small in the present weakly interacting regime (ρa 3 ) 1/2 ≪ 1 by choosing a lattice spacing much larger than a but still much smaller than the healing length ∝ 1/ √ ρa [CITATION_1] . In terms of the fields, the collective spin components are",
